laboratory_examinations.findings: ED showed gallbladder wall edema which could reflect mild hepatitis. Liver appears slightly hypoattenuating, possibly due to fatty deposition. No discrete focal liver lesion. Main portal vein patent. No biliary ductal dilation. Kidneys enhance symmetrically, equal contrast excretion. No worrisome renal lesion, hydronephrosis, or signs of pyelonephritis.
